rComments: Mr. Oxley, is an incredible professor I cannot stress enough how much of an impression he has had on me as a painter. If he sees you're dedicated, he will push you, and not just as a painter, but as an artist. An outstanding professor, and an incredible human being. It was such a joy to be a part of his class.

He is a knowledgeable professor and if approached will go out of his way to lend a helping hand. He is very opinionated and challenges a lot of the commentary made during crits, which is sometimes off puting but thought provoking. Nothing too extreme, work load is light and manageable, if kept up with!

How come the first comment is so mean?  If you ask questions, he helps you.  If he senses you're uncomfortable with suggestions, he respects that.  What's wrong with that?  He leaves the door open for you to take personal responsibility for how much you learn.  I think he's just fine!  I hope he doesn't take your comments seriously.
What an idiot.  Has he even painted before?
Knowledgeable, helpful and friendly, Art profs have always been my favorite and he is probably the best I've ever had.
